  "prompt": "Does the 112 emergency number work in the USA?",
  "response": "In the United States, the primary and official emergency telephone number is **911**. This number connects callers to emergency services such as police, fire departments, and medical assistance 24/7.\n\n**112** is the standard emergency number across many countries in the European Union and other regions around the world. While **112** is not officially designated as an emergency number in the U.S., some mobile phones may recognize **112** and automatically redirect the call to **911** as a safety measure. This redirection is part of efforts by mobile carriers to support international travelers who are accustomed to using **112** in their home countries.\n\nHowever, it's important to note the following:\n\n1. **Reliability:** Since **112** is not an officially recognized emergency number in the U.S., relying on it may not always guarantee a connection to emergency services. It's best to use **911** when in need of immediate assistance.\n\n2. **Awareness:** Not all devices or carriers may support the redirection from **112** to **911**, so it's crucial for individuals residing in or visiting the U.S. to be aware of and use the **911** system.\n\n3. **Emergency Situations:** In any emergency within the United States, dialing **911** is the most effective and reliable way to reach emergency responders quickly.\n\n**In summary:** While dialing **112** on some mobile phones in the United States might connect you to **911**, it is not the official emergency number in the U.S. For prompt and reliable assistance, always dial **911** when an emergency arises.",
